/*<!-- 
	The line below passes the directions and search service URLs into the map control.
	The services are on the plat server.  But the current Cosmos logging infrastructure depends on FrontDoor
	and requires that we hit the service through the appserver.  (We have a FrontDoor URL entry that redirects
	the service to the plat server.)  The current solution is to override the map control's DirectionService/SearchService
	URLs when the map control is hosted in the SNR map wrapper, using www.bing.com/maps instead if the plat server.
	We need to come up with a better solution for mapcontrol logging.
-->*/
if (Microsoft && Microsoft.Maps && Microsoft.Maps.Globals) {
	Microsoft.Maps.Globals.directionsService = "http://www.bing.com/maps/directions.ashx?";
	Microsoft.Maps.Globals.restAdvancedSearchService = "http://www.bing.com/maps/search.ashx";
}
